        "created_at": "2019-04-22T16:52:35.026Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"alexmiller\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"1314\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/alexmiller/48/326_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> alexmiller:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You are 100% correct. FDB only verify that the certificate is valid, and has the fields matching the <code>tls_verify_peers</code> string. The security model assumes that the certificates issued to clients are securely locked down. So if an attacker has a copy of one of the certificates, then they are allowed to re-use from any location at will.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That aligns with my findings.</p>\n<p>Any thoughts regarding my second question: Are there any plan to enable support for this automatic validation?</p>\n<p>It seems like implementing a feature to verify a server\u2019s IP address against a Subject Name Alternative IP should be possible. I can open a feature request to discuss it further but I wanted to check to make sure there wasn\u2019t already a plan to implement this (or some technical or philosophical reason for why it shouldn\u2019t be).</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"alexmiller\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"1314\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/alexmiller/48/326_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> alexmiller:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>( TLS as a plugin was removed in 6.0, and since is just compiled in by default. If you see any documentation text still talking about TLS as a plugin, please point it out so that we can fix the text. )</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Here are a a couple of references that appear to have been missed:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/backups.html?highlight=plugin\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Backup, Restore, and Replication for Disaster Recovery \u2014 FoundationDB 7.1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/configuration.html?highlight=plugin\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Configuration \u2014 FoundationDB 7.1</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let me know if you need me to open them as issues for tracking / remediation.</p>",
